<h1>LG Washer Lid Switch Replacement</h1>

<p>On a top-load LG washer, the lid switch tells the machine the lid is closed — and when it fails, the washer won't spin or won't start at all, because for safety it won't run with the lid unconfirmed. It's one of the more affordable LG washer repairs and a fast same-day fix. We replace the lid switch across LA — $180–260 with a one-year warranty. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Signs Your Lid Switch Has Failed</h2>
<p>The classic sign is a washer that fills and washes but won't spin, or won't start at all, even with the lid clearly shut. Sometimes you'll notice the lid no longer makes its usual click as it closes. Because the machine can't confirm the lid, it skips the spin or refuses to begin — behavior that shows up as an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-not-spinning/">LG washer that won't spin</a> or an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-not-starting/">LG washer that won't start</a>.</p>

<h2>How We Replace the Lid Switch</h2>
<p>Our techs test the switch for electrical continuity as the lid closes to confirm it's no longer registering, then replace the switch or lid-lock assembly with an OEM part. Before we leave, we run the machine to make sure the spin engages properly with the new switch in place. It's a quick job, about 30–60 minutes.</p>

<h2>Cost of Lid Switch Replacement</h2>
<p>Lid switch replacement runs $180–260 installed, which makes it one of the more affordable LG washer repairs. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. For how this fits among other LG washer prices, see our <a href="/washer/price-list/lg-washer-repair-cost/">LG washer repair cost</a> page.</p>

<h2>Why It Matters</h2>
<p>The lid switch is a safety interlock — it stops the drum from spinning while the lid is open, which on a top-loader is a real hazard. That's why we replace a failed switch rather than bypassing it: defeating the interlock leaves a spinning drum exposed, and we won't set up a machine that way.</p>

<h2>OEM Parts and Warranty</h2>
<p>We fit OEM lid switches, not generic substitutes that can fail again quickly, and back the work with a one-year warranty on parts and labor. There's no surcharge for same-day or weekend service.</p>

<p>Top-loader filling but not spinning? Our LG Dryer Repair techs test and replace the lid switch on-site across LA, Orange County, and Ventura County — most are same-day. Call (323) 990-7550; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Lid Switch Replacement</h2>

<h3>How do I know if my LG washer lid switch is bad?</h3>
<p>A failed lid switch on a top-load LG washer lets the machine fill and wash but stops it from spinning, or keeps it from starting at all — even with the lid closed. The washer can't confirm the lid is shut, so it won't run the spin for safety.</p>

<h3>How much does LG washer lid switch replacement cost?</h3>
<p>Lid switch replacement runs $180–260 installed, making it one of the more affordable LG washer repairs. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and the work has a one-year warranty. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Why won't my LG washer spin if the lid is closed?</h3>
<p>The lid switch is a safety interlock — the washer won't spin until the switch confirms the lid is shut. When the switch wears out, it stops registering the closed lid even though it looks shut, so the machine skips the spin. Replacing the switch restores it.</p>

<h3>Can I bypass the lid switch instead of replacing it?</h3>
<p>No — the lid switch is a safety device that stops the drum from spinning with the lid open, and defeating it is genuinely dangerous. We replace the switch so the safety works as designed rather than bypassing it.</p>

<h3>How long does LG washer lid switch replacement take?</h3>
<p>A lid switch replacement takes about 30–60 minutes, and we do it same-day in most cases. We test that the spin engages properly before we leave.</p>

